comments: This version contains additional, spoken French, lyrics. These are drawn from a letter, now in the public domain, written by the Breton poet laureat Anatole Le Braz (Tina Weymouth's great grandfather), to a young writer he was mentoring early in the last century: "La haine n'a jamais rien créé: seul l'amour est fécond. Comprendre c'est aimer et réciproquement. (In English: "Nothing was ever created from hate: only love is fecund. To understand is to love and vice versa.").
